---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Overview
description: Schema-derived reference docs and implementation guidance for the Aihio design system.
---
<section class="docs-hero">
  <div class="docs-hero__copy">
    <div class="docs-eyebrow">
      <aihio-badge>Schema-derived</aihio-badge>
      <aihio-badge variant="secondary">Eleventy docs</aihio-badge>
      <aihio-badge variant="outline">Zero-dependency components</aihio-badge>
    </div>

    <h1 class="docs-title">Design system docs that stay in sync with the source of truth.</h1>
    <p class="docs-lede">
      Aihio ships machine-readable component contracts, intent tokens, patterns, lint tooling, and MCP surfaces.
      This site reads those generated artifacts directly and uses the same components it documents.
    </p>

    <div class="docs-callouts">
      <aihio-alert>
        <div slot="title">Generated from build artifacts</div>
        <div slot="description">Component inventory, pattern counts, and API facts all come from the same schema emitted into <code>dist/</code>.</div>
      </aihio-alert>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-hero__preview">
    <aihio-card class="docs-hero-card">
      <aihio-card-header>
        <aihio-card-title>Reference Preview</aihio-card-title>
        <aihio-card-description>The docs shell is assembled with Aihio cards, badges, alerts, tabs, inputs, and buttons.</aihio-card-description>
      </aihio-card-header>
      <aihio-card-content>
        <form>
          <label class="docs-field">
            <span>Component search</span>
            <aihio-input placeholder="button, dialog, tabs"></aihio-input>
          </label>

          <div class="docs-chip-row">
            <aihio-badge variant="secondary">Attributes</aihio-badge>
            <aihio-badge variant="secondary">A11y contract</aihio-badge>
            <aihio-badge variant="secondary">Counterexamples</aihio-badge>
          </div>
        </form>
      </aihio-card-content>
      <aihio-card-footer>
        <aihio-button onclick="window.location.href='/components/'">Browse components</aihio-button>
        <aihio-button variant="outline" onclick="window.location.href='/components/'">View reference index</aihio-button>
      </aihio-card-footer>
    </aihio-card>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="docs-stat-grid">
  <div class="docs-stat-card">
    <strong>{{ docs.componentCount }}</strong>
    <span>Schema-backed components with generated runtime and type metadata.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="docs-stat-card">
    <strong>{{ docs.patternCount }}</strong>
    <span>Seeded composition patterns reused by docs, prompts, linting, and agent tooling.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="docs-stat-card">
    <strong>{{ docs.intentCount }}</strong>
    <span>Intent vocabulary entries mapping author meaning onto tokens and components.</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="docs-section-heading">
    <div>
      <h2>What This Site Covers</h2>
      <p>The first phase focuses on the overview shell and generated component index. Detail pages, patterns, and AI/tooling sections land next.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-feature-grid">
    <a class="docs-feature-card docs-feature-card--link" href="/components/">
      <h3>Component Reference</h3>
      <p>API facts, intents, examples, and accessibility obligations sourced from the generated schema.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="docs-feature-card docs-feature-card--link" href="/patterns/">
      <h3>Pattern Library</h3>
      <p>Higher-level markup compositions such as auth flows, settings panels, tabbed settings, and toast stacks.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="docs-feature-card docs-feature-card--link" href="/foundations/tokens/">
      <h3>Design Foundations</h3>
      <p>Intent-token vocabulary and the semantic bridge from raw values to component-facing roles.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="docs-feature-card docs-feature-card--link" href="/ai/">
      <h3>AI Tooling</h3>
      <p>Schema exports, linting, prompt fragments, and the local MCP server all documented in one place.</p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="docs-section-heading">
    <div>
      <h2>Featured Components</h2>
      <p>Phase 1 exposes the index first so the generated data model and docs shell are stable before per-component deep dives land.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="docs-inline-link" href="/components/">See the full component index</a>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-component-grid">
    {% for component in docs.featuredComponents %}
      {% include "partials/component-card.njk" %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
